tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE WeatherData (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    city VARCHAR(255),
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE weather_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  city VARCHAR(50),
  start_date DATE,
  end_date DATE,
  average_temperature FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE weather_forecast (
    city VARCHAR,
    date DATE,
    forecast VARCHAR,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE weather_comparison (
    city VARCHAR,
    date DATE,
    historical_temperature FLOAT,
    forecasted_temperature FLOAT,
    historical_humidity FLOAT,
    forecasted_humidity FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE weather_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    city VARCHAR(255),
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE temperature_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    city_id INT,
    min_temp FLOAT,
    max_temp FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE precipitation_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    city_id INT,
    precipitation FLOAT,
    weather_condition VARCHAR(255)
);
